{
  "texts": [
    "In graph pooling methods, the selection of hyperparameters is crucial to the model performance.",
    "For example, in node sampling methods, different pooling ratios can make a significant difference in the final graph representation (Li et al. 2021).",
    "Currently, the optimal pooling ratio in node sampling pooling methods often relies on previous experience to set, which is time-consuming and may lack generality.",
    "Although there have been research attempts to determine the optimal pooling ratio using reinforcement learning, the complexity of the training process and the additional parameters introduced have brought new challenges (Sun et al. 2021).",
    "Considering the large number of hyperparameters involved in the graph pooling process, hyperparameter sensitivity analysis naturally becomes a computationally intensive task."
  ]
}